headline: AutoZone (AZO): Taking Stock of Valuation After a Recent 3% Pullback in the Share Price
summary: AutoZone (AZO) has quietly pulled back about 3% over the past week even as its year to date gain sits near 18%, a classic setup for investors watching valuations and long term earnings power. See our latest analysis for AutoZone. That 3.1% weekly share price pullback comes after a strong year to date share price return of about 17.8% and a roughly 20% one year total shareholder return.
